  "doc_id": "15850",
  "text": "As described in [CITATION_1] , the mutation types were classified into nine categories: missense, nonsense, frameshift, synonymous, promoter, 3′UTR, small structural changes (in frame; <50 bp), splice site change, and large structural changes (>50 bp). The molecular defects resulting in these mutation types were listed under Mechanism. These included: substitution, deletion, duplication, insertion, and deletion/insertion, if a number of base pairs were deleted and extra base pairs were inserted in the same place in F9. Exon and codon identify the exons where the mutation is located and codons the mutation affects, respectively. The domains, which were defined based on [CITATION_2] , identify the domain locations of the mutation. The subtype of each mutation indicates the mutation locations in one of the following: promoter, signal peptide, propeptide, light chain, heavy chain, and 3′UTR.",
